{
  "stem": "15174.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And in October of 1942, three or four months after we left, the Germans came and they picked up-- they picked up all the Jews and sent them to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we heard after the war, because we communicated with this teacher-- my teacher, his teacher-- that his parents found out that-- somehow that they were going to be taken, and they asked the teacher to hide their son, Leon.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They hid him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But he was very attached to his mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And two days after the-- the Germans had picked up his parents, he just left the school and he went to the [FRENCH], to the police station.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he said, he told them he wanted to join his parents, and he did in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Another, as far as survivors are concerned, my mother had another brother who was living in Holland-- this was the youngest brother, [FRENCH].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we had-- she hadn't seen him for years, but we had-- she had corresponded with him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "After the war we tried to find him through the Red Cross, but we couldn't, they couldn't locate him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And so we assumed, of course, that he had been killed as well.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I traveled in Europe in 1963.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I was in Holland, and-- you know, I knew that my uncle had lived there, but I-- I-- I assumed he was dead.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "A few years later, my great uncle, my mother's uncle was also traveling in Europe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He was in Holland, and he was passing through Utrecht, which is where my uncle had lived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I don't know what possessed him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He opened the telephone book and looked for the name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "His name, because he was adopted, was Humburger.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And-- and he found a name and he called him, and it was him.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
